    "handoff_line": "MarginGate clears the compliant-500 budget iff the provable-stable skip rate \u2265 skip_rate_min_at_lambda1 = 0.9706 (\u03bb=1; 0.9712 at #71 spine 0.997); the researcher's 81\u201385% estimate MISSES and the 44% empirical floor MISSES (itself a CEILING \u2014 provably-stable \u2286 non-flip \u21d2 skip \u2264 0.4392 from #114's 56.08% flip rate), so the cheap verify_flip_probe diagnostic (measured margin distribution \u2192 skip_rate, \u03b5_max) is the single number that decides MarginGate \u2014 the highest-ranked (P=0.45) valid-verify path; standalone DVR fails at our 56.08% flip (Rank-4) and the MarginGate+DVR hybrid ALSO MISSES because a SOUND margin gate's skip set \u2286 non-flips, so its effective rollback = the full 56.08% flip rate (zero reduction). Lowest-overhead compliant route for any achievable skip stays the custom batch-invariant int4 kernel (#216). Adds 0 TPS; authorizes nothing; ARMS (does not run) verify_flip_probe. NOT a launch. NOT open2.",
